SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 965
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the West Valley Middle
School Lady Wolves girls' basketball team on
winning the Tennessee Middle School Athletic
Association Class 3A state championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should salute those student athletes who, through their
extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of whom we can all be
proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of young athletes is the West Valley Middle
School Lady Wolves girls' basketball team, whose members have all proven themselves to be
the fiercest of competitors and truly worthy of admiration by winning the 2026 Tennessee Middle
School Athletic Association Class 3A state championship, completing an undefeated 33-0
season, and claiming back-to-back state championships; and
WHEREAS, on their path to the state championship, the Lady Wolves triumphed over
Upperman in the semifinals in a hard-fought contest and rightfully earned the title of state
champion by defeating Mt. Juliet by a score of 38-24; and
WHEREAS, West Valley's superb performance would not have been possible without
the expert guidance of Coach Josh Ballard and the unfailing support of the players' families,
their fans, and their community; and
WHEREAS, the members of the West Valley Middle School girls' basketball team
epitomize all that is good in today's student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of
success in competition while exhibiting the highest degree of character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of
young women not only made possible a championship season but also surely bode well for their
future success; and
SJR0965
016235
- 1 -

WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and congratulate the members of the
West Valley Middle School girls' basketball team on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the members and coaches
of the West Valley Middle School Lady Wolves basketball team upon winning the TMSAA Class
3A state championship and extend to them our best wishes for every continued success in all
their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
